  "planned_workouts": [
    {
      "id": 101107292,
      "date": "2026-03-28",
      "name": "Leg Speed #1",
      "type": "WORKOUT",
      "sport_type": "Ride",
      "planned_tss": 53,
      "duration_hours": 0.97,
      "duration_formatted": "58m",
      "workout_summary": "5m @121W | 1m @111W | 5m @141W | 1m @111W | 10\u00d71m @178W / 2m rec | 1m @111W | 10m @162W | 5m @102W",
      "description": "In this low-intensity workout, we focus on leg speed today. The majority of the session is spent in zone 2. However, we hit some 1-minute high cadence efforts during the session.\n\nAll this then culminates with a steady-state zone 3 effort.\n\nWarmup\n- 30^ Today we are utilizing our time spent at a lower intensity by incorporating some high cadence efforts. 60^ This is a good day to build some volume for the week. 90^ With all of the work completed well under threshold, this is also a good fat burning day for you.<!> 5m ramp 50-69.9%\n\n- 20^ The warmup reflects the work you have ahead of you. 40^ Hence, it is a pretty low key warmup.<!> 1m 55%\n- 30^ We have a steady state effort to complete the warmup. 40^ Try to spin a little faster than what you are normally comfortable with during this effort. 60^ Relax your grip on the bars and spin the legs. 200^ Riding will often force you to pedal at a cadence that you are not comfortable with. 220^ These efforts today address this issue and also provide some quality aerobic work. 240^ The target power is not high, so you can just focus on the cadence.<!> 5m 69.9%\n- 20^ Remember to always hit the target cadence and let the smart trainer adjust the power. 50^ Here we go with the 1st effort.<!> 1m 55%\n\n10x\n- 1m 87.9%\n- 2m 73%\n\n- 10^ Just a quick recovery. 40^ The session is overall low intensity. 13578^ How much will these previous efforts influence your chosen cadence when there is no set target.<!> 1m 55%\n- 20^ Here we go with your steady state effort. 60^ Settle into a nice rhythm early. 120^ How is your cadence? 140^ Higher than you would normally ride at? 160^ Do you think the earlier efforts have influenced your cadence here? 300^ That's halfway for you. 400^ You can't beat the quality of a nice long steady state interval. 420^ It's basic, but effective. 500^ Think of the volume you're getting here today. 540^ Into the final minute now 560^ Did your cadence change much throughout the 10min?<!> 10m 80%\n- 30^ Although today was low intensity, be sure to hydrate and refuel adequately. 60^ From this session, you will be flying in the next workout.<!> 5m 50.4%"
    },
